<br>
Higher level players have all the advantages as it is. They have better spells, better resistances, better items, better hitpoints, better AC, better everything. So in essence, higher level players have the advantage by default.<br>
What the damage bonuses (or reductions) do is to promote fair play between players of different level. It puts both combatents on even ground, instead of handing victories to higher level players.<br>
Anyway, if you don't like lower level players attacking you, level up <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>4. Same. Resists are whacked enough as it is.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Again, it's to level the playing field.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>5. Bad idea there. City pvp can be fun and it would allow people to missuse certain strategies to a greater extent. a) zoning into a pvp safe zone to hide b) keeping an invulnerable healer in a safe zone to heal combatants as they get injured.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Zoning into a safe zone isn't hiding, it's retreating. In otherwords, you've won if your opponent retreats. This already happens with places like the nexus, and PoK. In fact, I see noobies actually playing (PvE) near PoK portals just so they don't have to deal with the PKs in the noobie/lowbie zones.<br>
The other thing you're forgetting about is this: If you're PvPing near a city zone, the guards are going to assist someone. Usually the one they see running, since the person running is not attacking the other player.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>don't you remember people who attack and kill you? Don't group much do ya?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Yeah, I know who the bad guys are, most of the time. The thing is, I've been playing for 3 and a half years, and it's a chore to have to keep a <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://ralloszek.stephans.org/">database</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> of people that have tried or successfully killed me. Not to mention that I'm sick of hearing guildies ask &quot;is X guild a PK guild?&quot;. It's pointless, and there should be some system of letting people know who is who.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>8-10 Unneccesary<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
You must not understand anything about grouping yourself if you think those suggestions are unneccesary. I can't use 3/4ths of my AE spells in groups because if I do, I hit my groupmates/guildmates/raidmates as well as hitting the monsters. It's a totally stupid rule that needs to be looked at. I should have full access to all of my spells, just as anybody on a blue server has full access to their spells.<br>
