 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jarnin>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Likes to wear<BR>Yoda Under-Roos</span><br>  Posts: 2717<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/28/03 11:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Comments</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>2) Item loot is fine leave it as is. No real reason to change it. If you wanna wear your fungi, you better be ready to bag it. Maybe there is a good reason for you wanting to do this?? I cant really think of one.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->3 reasons:<br>
<br>
1. True PvP'ers will PvP even if there is no item loot.<br>
<br>
2. The more restricted item loot rules are, the more relaxed players will be with PvP.<br>
<br>
3. With the Class/Race restrictions on looting in PvP, classes will migrate to PvPing with other players that may possibly have loot they can wear, which makes the battles a bit more even (Wiz vs. Enc/Mag/Nec/Wiz, Rogue vs. Rng/Shm/Rog, etc.)<br>
<br>
<br>
Another idea I've been tossing around is allowing No-Drop items to be looted in PvP. The idea is; So many people hide behind no-drop items that it ruins the idea of having item loot in the first place. With Class/Race restrictions, you'd only have to worry about players that can wear your items (same class or same armor type).<br>
No-Drop items would still have the same PvE rules (no drop, no trade). If you lose a no-drop item, you can bet that the person that got it is either wearing it, or destroyed it. They can't sell it, and they can't trade it. This might allow you the chance to get the item back in the future.<br>
<br>
The best armor for PvP would end up being cultural/religious armor that has a level requirement on it. That stuff would be about as no-drop as you'd get.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>However, I would be happy with the reduction cap being changed to 33% instead of 66%.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Erm, what do you mean? It is a 33% damage reduction, or 66% damage done. I'm pretty sure you didn't mean you want nukes to do 33% damage, cause that would be silly...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>4) Resists are so screwed up, i am afraid what they will screw up if they touch them. (ie. I can see them make tash lower 200mr if u are 4 levels below and them thinking it is fair.)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I updated the resistance rule so resist debuffs work better on higher level players. There's no change for lower level players.<br>
The idea behind this would be you go looking for higher level players to PvP against. That promotes learning PvP, because they're harder opponents.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I also would like to see an ability for a guild leader to make another guild KoS to them. That would be really cool.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->That'd be easy to do with the /guildwar command <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
