<br>
The idea went like so.<br>
<br>
New commands.<br>
<br>
/guildkos available only to officers this command marks a single enemy or entire guild as kos to your fellows.<br>
<br>
Usage: /guildkos Graffe /guildkos &quot;Graffe Mods&quot;<br>
<br>
/kos available to all this command marks an enemy or an entire guild as kos to you.<br>
<br>
The actual result would be that anyone in that guild (or just you) would see the person with a KOS tag in any /who or /who all listing as well as in person.  This tag would be very similar to the AFK tag. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=acillatemzoso>Acillatem Zoso</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 198<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/2/03 3:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 10 suggested changes for Rallos Zek PvP rules</span><hr size=1> Coming from Tallon here, so bear with the critique <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
1.  No comment - not needed on TZ IMO.<br>
<br>
2.  Again, not needed on TZ, however I see no reason to implement this anywayz.  If I kill someone, I would want a trophy, a mark of that kill and not be limited to looting someone who holds something I could USE.<br>
<br>
3. No.  Higher levels have an advantage for a reason.  It's called they EARNED it.  The gear, the levels, the AA's, the potions.  They are all a part of the PvP environment.  Those who take the time, and the energy to achieve all of the above, SHOULD have a significant advantage over Joe Blow with zero AAs, level 57, missing spells, wearing a Gossimmer Robe using no potions.  This idea only promotes laziness and takes away the &quot;spoils&quot; of achieving PvE goals in order to make yourself better in PvP.  If it's a fair fight yer looking for, /duel another 65 WIZ.<br>
<br>
4.  Again no.  A level 65 with &quot;Debuff of the Gods&quot; has EARNED the right to diminish my MR to nothingness.  Besides that, almost every debuff can be countered via potions or spells that a WIZ has anywayz.<br>
<br>
5.  I would imagine this is a problem on Rallos more than Tallon, however I frequently take my Human WIZ into Neriak to PvP unsuspecting Darks.  The prey is very few and far between since Luclin was released, however City PvP is some of the all time best PvP in EQ.  I can remember when I first started on Tallon Zek, Darks would raid Freeport, and Humans would rally from across the lands to hold it.  It was a weekly event, and was the best PvP I've ever had the chance to be in.<br>
<br>
Then they nerfed the guards~<br>
<br>
6.  Altho a nice idea, I think this is more of a novelty and not something really needed or useful.<br>
<br>
7.  See 6.<br>
<br>
8.  Good idea.  Altho simply pressing &lt;CTL&gt; &lt;D&gt; will nullify it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
9.  Must be a RZ thing.<br>
<br>
10.  Again, must be a RZ problem.<br>
<br>
<br>
The only &quot;lameness&quot; I've seen lately was people porting C3ers away from bazaar to gank their plat.  Perhaps something similar to yer No PvP group idea is to put a time restraint of 15 seconds after leaving group?<br>
<br>
Most of these I see no reason for on Tallon Zek.  Now if you can solve corpse camping, training, and bind rushing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
But as someone else said, Verant doesn't care.  Notice all of that became legal when Stormhammer was released?  Cuz they want you to get frustrated and leave your PvP server and pay 30 mroe dollars for a &quot;stress free&quot; game.<br>
